===Etymology===
{{etyl|ang}} ''[[blæd]]'' ‘leaf’, from {{proto|Germanic|blađan|leaf, blade}} (compare West Frisian {{term|bled|lang=fy}}, Dutch ''[[blad]]'', German ''[[Blatt]]''), from {{proto|Indo-European|bhlḥₐd-|leaf}} (compare Tocharian A/B ''pält/pilta'' 'leaf'), from *''bhel''- 'to thrive, bloom'. More at [[blow#Etymology_3|blow]].

